For the first time, The Queen’s Dineo and artists Zothile ‘Solo’ Langa who are in preparations of their second white wedding opened up about their relationship. Dineo revealed that she had to pay Lobola to Solo’s ancestors. “A message was conveyed to me through a dream, saying we first had to get our ancestors acquainted with each other, this would, in turn, help them co-exist peacefully going forward,” READ: DOCUMENTARY FILM FOR NEWLY WEDS SOLO AND DINEO LANGA The Langas also revealed that they are both called to be traditional healers and that is the foundation that has made their relationship sacred. They shared how important their ancestors and their callings were to the process and for those reasons they both paid lobola for each other to avoid friction between the two sides of their ancestral families. You Asked For It And Now It's Here. The Wedding Pictures And Our Story Wrapped Into One Incredible @truelovemagazine September Issue. A Moment Captured by @aust_malema. IN STORES TOMORROW!!! My Husband @thisissolo and I Hope You Enjoy It. With Love, From Us. A post shared by  Dineo Langa (@dineomoeketsi) on Aug 18, 2019 at 9:06am PDT  